message.content: Since the coefficient of $x^2$ is positive, the parabola $x^2 + 11x - 5$ opens upward, so the vertex gives the minimum value. The $x$-coordinate of the vertex is $-\frac{11}{2\cdot 1} = -\frac{11}{2},$ so the minimum value is $-\frac{11}{2} \cdot \frac{11}{2} - 5 = \boxed{-\frac{151}{4}}.$
